191  /* Note: We specifically omit the test for yy_rule_can_match_eol because it requires
192  * access to the local variable yy_act. Since yyless() is a macro, it would break
193  * existing scanners that call yyless() from OUTSIDE handlebars_yy_lex.
194  * One obvious solution it to make yy_act a global. I tried that, and saw
195  * a 5% performance hit in a non-yylineno scanner, because yy_act is
196  * normally declared as a register variable-- so it is not worth it.
197  */
198  #define YY_LESS_LINENO(n) \
199  do { \
200  int yyl;\
201  for ( yyl = n; yyl < yyleng; ++yyl )\
202  if ( yytext[yyl] == '\n' )\
203  --yylineno;\
204  }while(0)
205  #define YY_LINENO_REWIND_TO(dst) \
206  do {\
207  const char *p;\
208  for ( p = yy_cp-1; p >= (dst); --p)\
209  if ( *p == '\n' )\
210  --yylineno;\
211  }while(0)
212 
213 /* Return all but the first "n" matched characters back to the input stream. */
214 #define yyless(n) \
215  do \
216  { \
217  /* Undo effects of setting up yytext. */ \
218  int yyless_macro_arg = (n); \
219  YY_LESS_LINENO(yyless_macro_arg);\
220  *yy_cp = yyg->yy_hold_char; \
221  YY_RESTORE_YY_MORE_OFFSET \
222  yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yy_cp = yy_bp + yyless_macro_arg - YY_MORE_ADJ; \
223  YY_DO_BEFORE_ACTION; /* set up yytext again */ \
224  } \
225  while ( 0 )

253 
254  /* Whether this is an "interactive" input source; if so, and

257  * each newline.

259  int yy_is_interactive;

267  int yy_bs_lineno;

273  int yy_fill_buffer;
274 
275  int yy_buffer_status;

277 #define YY_BUFFER_NEW 0
278 #define YY_BUFFER_NORMAL 1
279  /* When an EOF's been seen but there's still some text to process
280  * then we mark the buffer as YY_EOF_PENDING, to indicate that we
281  * shouldn't try reading from the input source any more. We might
282  * still have a bunch of tokens to match, though, because of
283  * possible backing-up.
284  *
285  * When we actually see the EOF, we change the status to "new"
286  * (via handlebars_yy_restart()), so that the user can continue scanning by
287  * just pointing yyin at a new input file.
288  */
289 #define YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING 2
290 
291  };

5944 
5945  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_fill_buffer == 0 )
5946  { /* Don't try to fill the buffer, so this is an EOF. */
5947  if ( yyg->yy_c_buf_p - yyg->yytext_ptr - YY_MORE_ADJ == 1 )
5948  {
5949  /* We matched a single character, the EOB, so
5950  * treat this as a final EOF.
5951  */
5952  return EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
5953  }
5954 
5955  else
5956  {
5957  /* We matched some text prior to the EOB, first
5958  * process it.
5959  */
5960  return EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
5961  }
5962  }
5963 
5964  /* Try to read more data. */
5965 
5966  /* First move last chars to start of buffer. */
5967  number_to_move = (yy_size_t) (yyg->yy_c_buf_p - yyg->yytext_ptr) - 1;
5968 
5969  for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
5970  *(dest++) = *(source++);
5971 
5972  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
5973  /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
5974  * just force an EOF
5975  */
5976  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars = 0;
5977 
5978  else
5979  {
5980  yy_size_t num_to_read =
5981  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
5982 
5983  while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
5984  { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
5985 
5986  /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
5987  YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE;
5988 
5989  int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
5990  (int) (yyg->yy_c_buf_p - b->yy_ch_buf);
5991 
5992  if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
5993  {
5994  yy_size_t new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
5995 
5996  if ( new_size <= 0 )
5997  b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
5998  else
5999  b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
6000 
6001  b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
6002  /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
6003  handlebars_yy_realloc((void *) b->yy_ch_buf,b->yy_buf_size + 2 ,yyscanner );
6004  }
6005  else
6006  /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
6007  b->yy_ch_buf = 0;
6008 
6009  if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
6010  YY_FATAL_ERROR(
6011  "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
6012 
6013  yyg->yy_c_buf_p = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
6014 
6015  num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
6016  number_to_move - 1;
6017 
6018  }
6019 
6020  if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
6021  num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
6022 
6023  /* Read in more data. */
6024  YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
6025  yyg->yy_n_chars, num_to_read );
6026 
6027  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars;
6028  }
6029 
6030  if ( yyg->yy_n_chars == 0 )
6031  {
6032  if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
6033  {
6034  ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
6035  handlebars_yy_restart(yyin ,yyscanner);
6036  }
6037 
6038  else
6039  {
6040  ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
6041  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status =
6042  YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
6043  }
6044  }
6045 
6046  else
6047  ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
6048 
6049  if ((int) (yyg->yy_n_chars + number_to_move) > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size) {
6050  /* Extend the array by 50%, plus the number we really need. */
6051  int new_size = yyg->yy_n_chars + number_to_move + (yyg->yy_n_chars >> 1);
6052  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf = (char *) handlebars_yy_realloc((void *) YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf,new_size ,yyscanner );
6053  if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
6054  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_get_next_buffer()" );
6055  }
6056 
6057  yyg->yy_n_chars += number_to_move;
6058  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6059  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6060 
6061  yyg->yytext_ptr = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
6062 
6063  return ret_val;
6064 }

6067 
6068  static yy_state_type yy_get_previous_state (yyscan_t yyscanner)
6069 {
6070  yy_state_type yy_current_state;
6071  char *yy_cp;
6072  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6073 
6074  yy_current_state = yy_start_state_list[yyg->yy_start];
6075 
6076  for ( yy_cp = yyg->yytext_ptr + YY_MORE_ADJ; yy_cp < yyg->yy_c_buf_p; ++yy_cp )
6077  {
6078  yy_current_state += yy_current_state[(*yy_cp ? YY_SC_TO_UI(*yy_cp) : 256)].yy_nxt;
6079  if ( yy_current_state[-1].yy_nxt )

6083  }
6084  }
6085

6089 /* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
6090  *
6091  * synopsis
6092  * next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
6093  */
6094  static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans (yy_state_type yy_current_state , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6095 {
6096  int yy_is_jam;
6097  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner; /* This var may be unused depending upon options. */
6098  char *yy_cp = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
6099 
6100  int yy_c = 256;
6101  yyconst struct yy_trans_info *yy_trans_info;
6102 
6103  yy_trans_info = &yy_current_state[(unsigned int) yy_c];
6104  yy_current_state += yy_trans_info->yy_nxt;
6105  yy_is_jam = (yy_trans_info->yy_verify != yy_c);
6106 
6107  if ( ! yy_is_jam )
6108  {
6109  if ( yy_current_state[-1].yy_nxt )
6110  {
6111  yyg->yy_last_accepting_state = yy_current_state;
6112  yyg->yy_last_accepting_cpos = yy_cp;
6113  }
6114  }
6115 
6116  (void)yyg;
6117  return yy_is_jam ? 0 : yy_current_state;
6118 }

6122  static void yyunput (int c, char * yy_bp , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6123 {

6125  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6126 
6127  yy_cp = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
6128 
6129  /* undo effects of setting up yytext */
6130  *yy_cp = yyg->yy_hold_char;
6131 
6132  if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
6133  { /* need to shift things up to make room */
6134  /* +2 for EOB chars. */
6135  yy_size_t number_to_move = yyg->yy_n_chars + 2;
6136  char *dest = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[
6137  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size + 2];
6138  char *source =
6139  &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move];
6140 
6141  while ( source > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
6142  *--dest = *--source;
6143 
6144  yy_cp += (int) (dest - source);
6145  yy_bp += (int) (dest - source);
6146  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars =
6147  yyg->yy_n_chars = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size;
6148 
6149  if ( yy_cp < YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
6150  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "flex scanner push-back overflow" );
6151  }
6152 
6153  *--yy_cp = (char) c;
6154 
6155  if ( c == '\n' ){
6156  --yylineno;
6157  }
6158 
6159  yyg->yytext_ptr = yy_bp;
6160  yyg->yy_hold_char = *yy_cp;
6161  yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yy_cp;
6162 }

6166 #ifndef YY_NO_INPUT
6167 #ifdef __cplusplus
6168  static int yyinput (yyscan_t yyscanner)
6169 #else
6170  static int input (yyscan_t yyscanner)
6171 #endif
6172 
6173 {
6174  int c;
6175  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6176 
6177  *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yy_hold_char;
6178 
6179  if ( *yyg->yy_c_buf_p == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
6180  {
6181  /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
6182  * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
6183  * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
6184  */
6185  if ( yyg->yy_c_buf_p < &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars] )
6186  /* This was really a NUL. */
6187  *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = '\0';
6188 
6189  else
6190  { /* need more input */
6191  yy_size_t offset = yyg->yy_c_buf_p - yyg->yytext_ptr;
6192  ++yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
6193 
6194  switch ( yy_get_next_buffer( yyscanner ) )
6195  {
6196  case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
6197  /* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
6198  * sees that we've accumulated a
6199  * token and flags that we need to
6200  * try matching the token before
6201  * proceeding. But for input(),
6202  * there's no matching to consider.
6203  * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
6204  * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
6205  */
6206 
6207  /* Reset buffer status. */
6208  handlebars_yy_restart(yyin ,yyscanner);
6209 
6210  /*FALLTHROUGH*/
6211 
6212  case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
6213  {
6214  if ( handlebars_yy_wrap(yyscanner ) )
6215  return EOF;
6216 
6217  if ( ! yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof )
6218  YY_NEW_FILE;
6219 #ifdef __cplusplus
6220  return yyinput(yyscanner);
6221 #else
6222  return input(yyscanner);
6223 #endif
6224  }
6225 
6226  case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
6227  yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yytext_ptr + offset;
6228  break;
6229  }
6230  }
6231  }
6232 
6233  c = *(unsigned char *) yyg->yy_c_buf_p; /* cast for 8-bit char's */
6234  *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = '\0'; /* preserve yytext */
6235  yyg->yy_hold_char = *++yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
6236 
6237  if ( c == '\n' )
6238 
6239  do{ yylineno++;
6240  yycolumn=0;
6241  }while(0)
6242 ;
6243 
6244  return c;
6245 }
6246 #endif /* ifndef YY_NO_INPUT */

6253  void handlebars_yy_restart (FILE * input_file , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6254 {
6255  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6256 
6257  if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ){
6258  handlebars_yy_ensure_buffer_stack (yyscanner);
6259  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE =
6260  handlebars_yy__create_buffer(yyin,YY_BUF_SIZE ,yyscanner);
6261  }
6262 
6263  handlebars_yy__init_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER,input_file ,yyscanner);
6264  handlebars_yy__load_buffer_state(yyscanner );
6265 }

6271  void handlebars_yy__switch_to_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6272 {
6273  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6274 
6275  /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
6276  * with
6277  * handlebars_yy_pop_buffer_state();
6278  * handlebars_yy_push_buffer_state(new_buffer);
6279  */
6280  handlebars_yy_ensure_buffer_stack (yyscanner);
6281  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
6282  return;
6283 
6284  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
6285  {
6286  /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
6287  *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yy_hold_char;
6288  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
6289  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars;
6290  }
6291 
6292  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
6293  handlebars_yy__load_buffer_state(yyscanner );
6294 
6295  /* We don't actually know whether we did this switch during
6296  * EOF (handlebars_yy_wrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
6297  * is looked at is after handlebars_yy_wrap() is called, so it's safe
6298  * to go ahead and always set it.
6299  */
6300  yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof = 1;
6301 }

6308  yyin = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_input_file;
6309  yyg->yy_hold_char = *yyg->yy_c_buf_p;

6362 /* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
6363  * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
6364  * such as during a handlebars_yy_restart() or at EOF.
6365  */
6366  static void handlebars_yy__init_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b, FILE * file , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6367 
6368 {

6372  handlebars_yy__flush_buffer(b ,yyscanner);
6373 
6374  b->yy_input_file = file;
6375  b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
6376 
6377  /* If b is the current buffer, then handlebars_yy__init_buffer was _probably_
6378  * called from handlebars_yy_restart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
6379  * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
6380  */
6381  if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
6382  b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
6383  b->yy_bs_column = 0;
6384  }
6385 
6386  b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
6387

6395  void handlebars_yy__flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6396 {

6398  if ( ! b )
6399  return;
6400

6402

6404  * a transition to the end-of-buffer state. The second causes
6405  * a jam in that state.
6406  */
6407  b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6408  b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
6409 
6410  b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
6411 
6412  b->yy_at_bol = 1;
6413  b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
6414 
6415  if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
6416  handlebars_yy__load_buffer_state(yyscanner );

6425 void handlebars_yy_push_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6426 {

6428  if (new_buffer == NULL)
6429  return;
6430 
6431  handlebars_yy_ensure_buffer_stack(yyscanner);
6432 
6433  /* This block is copied from handlebars_yy__switch_to_buffer. */
6434  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
6435  {
6436  /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
6437  *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yy_hold_char;
6438  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
6439  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars;
6440  }
6441

6443  if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
6444  yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top++;
6445  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;

6456 void handlebars_yy_pop_buffer_state (yyscan_t yyscanner)
6457 {

6459  if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
6460  return;
6461 
6462  handlebars_yy__delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ,yyscanner);
6463  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
6464  if (yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top > 0)
6465  --yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top;
6466 
6467  if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
6468  handlebars_yy__load_buffer_state(yyscanner );
6469  yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof = 1;
6470  }

6473 /* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
6474  * Guarantees space for at least one push.
6475  */
6476 static void handlebars_yy_ensure_buffer_stack (yyscan_t yyscanner)
6477 {
6478  yy_size_t num_to_alloc;
6479  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6480 
6481  if (!yyg->yy_buffer_stack) {
6482 
6483  /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
6484  * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
6485  * immediate realloc on the next call.
6486  */
6487  num_to_alloc = 1; /* After all that talk, this was set to 1 anyways... */
6488  yyg->yy_buffer_stack = (struct yy_buffer_state**)handlebars_yy_alloc
6489  (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
6490  , yyscanner);
6491  if ( ! yyg->yy_buffer_stack )
6492  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in handlebars_yy_ensure_buffer_stack()" );
6493 
6494  memset(yyg->yy_buffer_stack, 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
6495 
6496  yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max = num_to_alloc;
6497  yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top = 0;
6498  return;
6499  }
6500 
6501  if (yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top >= (yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max) - 1){
6502 
6503  /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
6504  yy_size_t grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
6505 
6506  num_to_alloc = yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max + grow_size;
6507  yyg->yy_buffer_stack = (struct yy_buffer_state**)handlebars_yy_realloc
6508  (yyg->yy_buffer_stack,
6509  num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
6510  , yyscanner);
6511  if ( ! yyg->yy_buffer_stack )
6512  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in handlebars_yy_ensure_buffer_stack()" );
6513 
6514  /* zero only the new slots.*/
6515  memset(yyg->yy_buffer_stack + yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max, 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
6516  yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max = num_to_alloc;
6517  }
6518 }

6526 YY_BUFFER_STATE handlebars_yy__scan_buffer (char * base, yy_size_t size , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6527 {
6528  YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
6529 
6530  if ( size < 2 ||
6531  base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
6532  base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
6533  /* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
6534  return 0;

6536  b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) handlebars_yy_alloc(sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) ,yyscanner );

6606  static void yy_push_state (int _new_state , yyscan_t yyscanner)
6607 {

6609  if ( yyg->yy_start_stack_ptr >= yyg->yy_start_stack_depth )
6610  {

6612

6614  new_size = yyg->yy_start_stack_depth * sizeof( int );
6615 
6616  if ( ! yyg->yy_start_stack )
6617  yyg->yy_start_stack = (int *) handlebars_yy_alloc(new_size ,yyscanner );
6618

6621

6624  }

6627

6847 /* handlebars_yy_lex_init is special because it creates the scanner itself, so it is
6848  * the ONLY reentrant function that doesn't take the scanner as the last argument.
6849  * That's why we explicitly handle the declaration, instead of using our macros.
6850  */
6851 
6852 int handlebars_yy_lex_init(yyscan_t* ptr_yy_globals)
6853 
6854 {
6855  if (ptr_yy_globals == NULL){
6856  errno = EINVAL;
6857  return 1;
6858  }
6859 
6860  *ptr_yy_globals = (yyscan_t) handlebars_yy_alloc ( sizeof( struct yyguts_t ), NULL );
6861 
6862  if (*ptr_yy_globals == NULL){
6863  errno = ENOMEM;
6864  return 1;
6865  }
6866 
6867  /* By setting to 0xAA, we expose bugs in yy_init_globals. Leave at 0x00 for releases. */
6868  memset(*ptr_yy_globals,0x00,sizeof(struct yyguts_t));
6869 
6870  return yy_init_globals ( *ptr_yy_globals );
6871 }

6873 /* handlebars_yy_lex_init_extra has the same functionality as handlebars_yy_lex_init, but follows the
6874  * convention of taking the scanner as the last argument. Note however, that
6875  * this is a *pointer* to a scanner, as it will be allocated by this call (and
6876  * is the reason, too, why this function also must handle its own declaration).
6877  * The user defined value in the first argument will be available to handlebars_yy_alloc in
6878  * the yyextra field.
6879  */
6880 
6881 int handlebars_yy_lex_init_extra(YY_EXTRA_TYPE yy_user_defined,yyscan_t* ptr_yy_globals )
6882 
6883 {

6889  errno = EINVAL;
6890  return 1;
6891  }
6892

6896  errno = ENOMEM;

6910 {

6942 /* handlebars_yy_lex_destroy is for both reentrant and non-reentrant scanners. */
6943 int handlebars_yy_lex_destroy (yyscan_t yyscanner)
6944 {
6945  struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
6946 
6947  /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
6948  while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
6949  handlebars_yy__delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ,yyscanner );
6950  YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
6951  handlebars_yy_pop_buffer_state(yyscanner);
6952  }
6953 
6954  /* Destroy the stack itself. */
6955  handlebars_yy_free(yyg->yy_buffer_stack ,yyscanner);
6956  yyg->yy_buffer_stack = NULL;
6957 
6958  /* Destroy the start condition stack. */
6959  handlebars_yy_free(yyg->yy_start_stack ,yyscanner );
6960  yyg->yy_start_stack = NULL;
6961 
6962  /* Reset the globals. This is important in a non-reentrant scanner so the next time
6963  * handlebars_yy_lex() is called, initialization will occur. */
6964  yy_init_globals( yyscanner);
6965 
6966  /* Destroy the main struct (reentrant only). */
6967  handlebars_yy_free ( yyscanner , yyscanner );
6968  yyscanner = NULL;
6969  return 0;
6970 }
